{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Sync to compliance-copilot",
  "description": "Manually sync recent changes from STIP-KaleAnalyzer and/or STIP-KaleMCP to the generic compliance-copilot project. Strips all Amazon-internal references and maps module names. Click the play button in the Agent Hooks panel to run.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "The user wants to sync recent changes to compliance-copilot. Check the git diff in BOTH STIP-KaleAnalyzer and STIP-KaleMCP to find uncommitted or recent changes, then port them to compliance-copilot. Refer to the compliance-copilot-sync steering rules for full sanitization details.\n\n## Module Mapping (STIP-KaleAnalyzer)\n- kale_data_extractor/ → compliance_extractor/\n- kale_reviewer/ → compliance_reviewer/\n- lambdas/ → lambdas/\n- scripts/ → scripts/\n- tests/ → tests/\n- infrastructure/ → infrastructure/\n\n## Module Mapping (STIP-KaleMCP)\n- STIP-KaleMCP/src/STIP-KaleMCP/src/stip_kale_mcp/ → compliance_mcp/\n- STIP-KaleMCP/src/STIP-KaleMCP/src/stip_kale_mcp/tools/ → compliance_mcp/tools/\n- STIP-KaleMCP/src/STIP-KaleMCP/test/ → tests/ (MCP-related tests)\n\n## Sanitization Rules\n1. Replace all references to \"Kale\" with \"Compliance\" (or appropriate generic term)\n2. Replace \"STIP\" with nothing or a generic project name\n3. Remove any Amazon-internal URLs (*.amazon.com, *.amazon.dev, *.a2z.com)\n4. Remove references to internal services (Midway, Bindles, Odin, Apollo, etc.)\n5. Replace internal auth mechanisms with generic placeholders\n6. Remove any internal team names, aliases, or org references\n7. Keep the core logic and patterns intact — only strip identifying details\n8. Update import paths: kale_data_extractor → compliance_extractor, kale_reviewer → compliance_reviewer, stip_kale_mcp → compliance_mcp\n9. MCP tool names: kale_lookup → compliance_lookup, kale_review → compliance_review, kale_findings → compliance_findings, kale_stats → compliance_stats\n\n## Process\n1. Run git diff and git diff --cached in both STIP-KaleAnalyzer and STIP-KaleMCP\n2. If no uncommitted changes, check git log for recent commits not yet synced\n3. Identify the corresponding files in compliance-copilot\n4. Apply the equivalent changes with full sanitization (strip all internal references)\n5. If a file doesn't exist yet in compliance-copilot, create it (sanitized)\n6. Run any existing tests in compliance-copilot to verify nothing broke"
  }
}
